{"lemma":"حَيْران","slug":"حَيْران","root":"ح.#.ر","root_slug":"ح-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَيْران","root":"حير","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9726"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"perplexed, confounded, astonished","examples":[{"text":"بُسَيْطَةُ مَهْلًا سُقِيتِ الْقِطَارَا / تَرَكْتِ عُيُونَ عَبِيدِي حَيَارَى"},{"text":"زَادَتِ ٱلْأَشْجَانُ فِي ٱلْهَوَى ٱلْعُذْرِيِّ / وَأَنَا ٱلْحَيْرَانُ كَاتِمُ ٱلسِّرِّ"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħaj.raːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9726","headword_ar":"حَيْرَانُ","root":"Hyr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAy^irN","text_ar":"حَايِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaHay~irN","text_ar":"مُتَحَيِّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexity, and unable to see his right course:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"erring; having lost his way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) fem. [of the first]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayoraY","text_ar":"حَيْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, T) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayoraA='u","text_ar":"حَيْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, K:) and pl. [of the same]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaAraY","text_ar":"حَيَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuyaAraY","text_ar":"حُيَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayoraY","text_ar":"حَيْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", like the fem. sing. (Lh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tafoEalo *`lika A^um~uka HayoraY","text_ar":"لَا تَفْعَلْ ذٰلِكَ اُمُّكَ حَيْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do not thou that: may thy mother become in a state of confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tafoEaluwA *`lika A^um~ahaAtukumo HayoraY","text_ar":"لَا تَفْعَلُوا ذٰلِكَ اُمَّهَاتُكُمْ حَيْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do not ye that: may your mothers become"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Lh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAy^irN","text_ar":"بَايِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN HaAy^irN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ حَايِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who does not apply himself rightly to an affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who knows not the right course to pursue in his affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^amorihi","text_ar":"فِى اَمْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaHay~irN","text_ar":"مُتَحَيِّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See also the same phrase in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hwr","text_ar":"حور"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoDpN HayoraY","text_ar":"رَوْضةٌ حَيْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A meadow full of water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayoraY","text_ar":"حَيْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied as an epithet to the midday sun of summer: see a verse cited in the second paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dwm","text_ar":"دوم"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["T","S","A","K","TA","Lh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}